No refuse removal will take place in the Greater Oudtshoorn today (27 April), a public holiday. Refuse collection will re-start tomorrow morning (28 April), also for areas that would have been covered today.Refuse removal will also not take place on Monday 1 May, as it is also a public holiday. Refuse collection will continue on Tuesday (2 May), also collecting Monday&#8217;s refuse.The municipality requested residents not to put out refuse bags prior to the days of refuse removal.